using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // Define a lambda expression to compute the sum of two numbers
        Func<double, double, double> add = (x, y) => x + y;

        // Input two numbers from the user
        Console.Write("Enter the first number: ");
        double num1 = Convert.ToDouble(Console.ReadLine());

        Console.Write("Enter the second number: ");
        double num2 = Convert.ToDouble(Console.ReadLine());

        // Compute the sum using the lambda expression
        double sum = add(num1, num2);

        // Display the sum to the user
        Console.WriteLine($"The sum of {num1} and {num2} is {sum}.");
    }
}









In this code:

We define a lambda expression add of type Func<double, double, double> that takes two double parameters x and y, and returns their sum.
We input two numbers from the user.
We invoke the lambda expression add with the provided numbers to compute their sum.
Finally, we display the computed sum to the user.
